00:12:06.080 --> 00:12:14.320
But he won 40% of the overall popular vote,
including majorities in many of the most populous
states, thereby winning the electoral college.

00:12:14.320 --> 00:12:19.560
So, anytime a guy becomes President who
literally did not appear on your ballot, there is
likely to be a problem.

00:12:19.560 --> 00:12:24.160
And indeed, Lincoln’s election led to a number
of Southern states seceding from the Union.

00:12:24.160 --> 00:12:30.160
Lincoln himself hated slavery, but he repeatedly said that he would leave it alone in the states where it existed.

00:12:30.160 --> 00:12:37.900
But the demographics of Lincoln’s election showed
Southerners and Northerners alike that slave power
– to whatever extent it had existed –was over.

00:12:37.900 --> 00:12:44.720
By the time he took office on March 1, 1861,
seven states had seceded and formed the
Confederate States of America.

00:12:44.720 --> 00:12:54.360
And the stage was set for the fighting to begin, which it did, when Southern troops fired upon the Union garrison at Fort Sumter in Charleston harbor on April 12, 1861.

00:12:54.360 --> 00:13:02.200
So, that’s when the Civil War started, but it
became inevitable earlier – maybe in 1857,
or maybe in 1850, or maybe in 1776.

00:13:02.200 --> 00:13:06.460
Or maybe in 1619, when the first African
slaves arrived in Virginia.

00:13:06.460 --> 00:13:14.720
Because here’s the thing: In the Dred Scott decision,
Chief Justice Taney said that black Americans had
“no rights which the white man was bound to respect.”

00:13:14.720 --> 00:13:17.000
But this was demonstrably false.

00:13:17.000 --> 00:13:21.020
Black men had voted in elections and
held property, including even slaves.

00:13:21.020 --> 00:13:24.540
They’d appeared in court on their own
behalf. They had rights.

00:13:24.540 --> 00:13:27.260
They’d expressed those rights when given
the opportunity.

00:13:27.260 --> 00:13:37.400
And the failure of the United States to understand that the rights of black Americans were as inalienable as those of white Americans is ultimately what made the Civil War inevitable.

